title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1994-07-21
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey, Greatest Story Ever Told, Jack A Roe, The Same Thing, Stagger Lee, Me & My Uncle->*, Mexicali Blues*, Ramble On Rose, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Women Are Smarter, If The Shoe Fits, Way to Go Home, Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Drums-> Space-> All Along The Watchtower-> The Days Between-> Good Lovin', E: Liberty

* Weir on acoustic guitar

reviews.review_text:
Singing Very nice recording - thank you. 
While Jerry's guitar playing started faltering for good around this time he had done something with his singing to where he was trying all sorts of different phrasing. His voice was clean and expressive. Little nuances that were so cool. Check out "Franklin's Tower." You can hear the crowd's acknowledgement.
